deck: The city is under attack. Can the new recruits save the day? Some will live, some will die, hidden feelings are revealed, and new information is revealed about the world outside the walls.
description:
Japanese title: Uijin -Torosuto-ku Kōbōsen (1)- (初陣　―トロスト区攻防戦①―)

Eren learns that, contrary to previous beliefs, the titans do possess intelligence. But when Eren attacks one, it vanishes in a cloud of steam.

We learn that the titans are almost all male in form, though they possess no sex organs and it is unknown how they reproduce. Also the titans seem to radiate a great deal of heat. They can go for very long periods without eating humans, so it is believed that their appetite for humans is more for bloodlust than for sustenance.

The Trost District is evacuated as volleys of cannon fire try to stop more titans from entering the city. The new recruits have conflicting emotions when first presented with real combat and seeing friends die.
name: First Battle: Battle of Trost District, Part 1

deck: Armin wakes up to Conny Springer, Christa Lenz and Ymir standing over him.
description:
Japanese title: Shōjo ga Mita Sekai -Torosuto-ku Kōbōsen (2)- (少女が見た世界　―トロスト区攻防戦②―)

The "she" referred to in the title "The The World She Saw: Battle of Trost District, Part 2" is Mikasa. This episode tells her back story.

When Armin comes to, he is surrounded by Conny Springer, Christa Lenz and Ymir. Armin breaks into tears when Conny asks what happened to his squad. Ymir realizes that they're dead. Armin blames himself for failing to save Eren.

Elsewhere, a merchant tries to force a cargo wagon through the city gate, blocking the way for people to evacuate. The crowd is terrified when an abnormal titan charges at them. At the last minute, Mikasa slays it. Then she deals with the merchant. This makes her flashback to her own childhood experiences with greedy slavers.
name: The World She Saw: Battle of Trost District, Part 2

deck: Mikasa must find the will to continue fighting.
description:
Japanese title: Chiisana Yaiba -Torosuto-ku Kōbōsen (3)- (小さな刃　―トロスト区攻防戦③―)

A handful of fighters remain outside the inner wall in the titan ravaged city. They're out of gas and the refilling at the depot is too dangerous. Armin tells Mikasa that his squad is dead, and Eren died trying to save him. Mikasa calls the rest cowards and sets off to tackle the titans alone, but soon runs out of gas and crashes to the street. As Mikasa lies cornered and vulnerable to attack by an approaching titan, she reflects back on events and struggles with whether it's even worth fighting anymore.
name: The Small Blade: Battle of Trost District, Part 3

description: Japanese title: Shinzō no Kodō ga Kikoeru -Torosuto-ku Kōbōsen (4)-(心臓の鼓動が聞こえる ―トロスト区攻防戦④―)
name: Hearing the Heartbeat: Battle of Trost District, Part 4

description:
Japanese title: Hidariude no Yukue -Torosuto-ku Kōbōsen (5)- 左腕の行方 ―トロスト区攻防戦⑤―

A miraculous return is met with anger and fear. Cannons are fixed on Eren as he struggles to remember what happened to him inside the belly of a monster and how he ended up humankind's enemy. One question is all that matters: is Eren human or Titan?
name: Where the Left Arm Went: Battle of Trost District, Part 5

description:
Japanese title: Kotaeru -Torosuto-ku Kōbōsen (6)- 応える ―トロスト区攻防戦⑥―

Cadets respond to Eren's terrifying transformation with doubt and fear as he struggles to understand it himself. If Armin can't talk the commander into using Eren's newfound powers for the good of humankind, all hope of stopping the Titans might be lost.
name: Answer: Battle of Trost District, Part 6

description:
Japanese title: Guuzou -Torosuto-ku Kōbōsen (7)- 偶像 ―トロスト区攻防戦⑦―

Plans are created to use Eren's Titan powers to seal the hole in the wall in an attempt reclaim Trost. But with the government's bloodstained history and vocal dissenters in the military ranks, the biggest threat to humankind may not be the Titans.
name: Icon: Battle of Trost District, Part 7

description:
Japanese title: Kizu -Torosuto-ku Kōbōsen (8)- (傷 ―トロスト区攻防戦⑧―)

The plan to reclaim Trost falls apart when Eren's newfound powers turn him into a mindless giant. As Titans continue to swarm the city, it's up to Armin and Mikasa to make sure the cadets massacred during the mission haven't died in vain.
name: Wound: Battle of Trost District, Part 8

description:
Japanese title: Genshoteki Yokkyū -Torosuto-ku Kōbōsen (9)- (原初的欲求 ―トロスト区攻防戦⑨―)

Jean takes desperate measures to replace his broken maneuvering device. Meanwhile, Eren is able to plug the hole in the wall thanks to the help of his fellow cadets, but the cost of humanity's first victory against the Titans will be gigantic.
name: Primal Desires: Battle of Trost District, Part 9

description:
Japanese title: Mada Me o Mirenai -Hangeki Zen'ya (1)- (まだ目を見れない ―反撃前夜①―)

A special military tribunal will decide Eren's fate. The Military Police calls for his execution while the Scout Regiment argues that he is a powerful resource for humankind, and Mikasa is put on the spot when asked about the events of the Trost mission.
name: Still Can't See: Prelude to the Counterattack, Part 1

description:
Japanese title: Tokubetsu Sakusen-han -Hangeki Zen'ya (2)- (特別作戦班 ―反撃前夜②―)

The Scout Regiment moves Eren to an old abandoned castle where he will continue his training. Hanzi visits and reveals that she's been putting two captured Titans through a series of tests and trials—experiments that she wants Eren's help with.
name: Special Operations Squad: Prelude to the Counterattack, Part 2

deck: Someone killed the titan prisoner and nobody knows who or why. Meanwhile a plan is hatched to retrieve information from the Trost District that may lead to the titan's downfall.
description:
Japanese title: Ima, Nani o Subeki ka -Hangeki Zen'ya (3)- (今、何をすべきか ―反撃前夜③―)

Everyone is a suspect in the investigation to find out who killed the two test-subject Titans. Meanwhile, the Cadets pick which corps they'll be joining, but after the harrowing events in the Trost attack, many are uncertain which branch to choose.

There may be information that can give the humans an edge located in the basement of a house in Shinganshina, but to get to it the scout regiment has to take a long route through enemy territory.
name: What Should be Done: Prelude to the Counterattack, Part 3

description:
Japanese title: Megata no Kyojin -Dai Gojū-Nana Kai Hekigai Chōsa (1)- (女型の巨人 ―第57回壁外調査①―)

As the Scout Regiment begins its push toward Shiganshina, they encounter an intelligent Female Titan unlike any they've seen before. When Armin hypothesizes that it’s really a human that’s been turned into a Titan, he, Jean, and Reiner attempt to stop it.
name: Female Titan: 57th Expedition Beyond the Walls, Part 1

description:
Japanese title: Kyodaiju no Mori -Dai Gojū-Nana Kai Hekigai Chōsa (2)- (巨大樹の森 ―第57回壁外調査②―)

As the Female Titan continues to tear its way through the Scout Regiment, Levi makes a bold decision to split the ranks and send Eren and the supply wagons through a huge forest. Is his strategy genius, or does is spell certain death for the scouts?
name: Forest of Giant Trees: 57th Expedition Beyond the Walls, Part 2

description:
Japanese title: Kamitsuku -Dai Gojū-Nana Kai Hekigai Chōsa (3)- (噛み付く ―第57回壁外調査③―)

A memory of Eren testing out his Titan powers sheds new light on how his abilities work. As the Female Titan continues to slaughter members of the Scout Regiment, Eren is faced with a difficult decisions: does he trust his teammates or act out on his own?
name: Bite: 57th Expedition Beyond the Walls, Part 3

description:
Japanese title: Eruvin Sumisu -Dai Gojū-Nana Kai Hekigai Chōsa (4) (エルヴィン・スミス ―第57回壁外調査④―)

The Female Titan has been captured, and it’s Erwin’s goal to find out who the human is lurking inside it. Meanwhile, the Scouts realize that the reason Levi told no one about their true mission outside the wall is because there is a spy among their ranks.
name: Erwin Smith: 57th Expedition Beyond the Walls, Part 4

description:
Japanese title: Tettsui -Dai Gojū-Nana Kai Hekigai Chōsa (5)- (鉄槌 ―第57回壁外調査⑤―)

A traitor has infiltrated the Scout Regiment, destroying their ranks from within. When cornered, she once again takes the form of the Female Titan—but this time, Eren’s not going to let her get away without one insanely brutal fight.
name: Crushing Blow: 57th Expedition Beyond the Walls, Part 5

description:
Japanese title: Haisha-tachi -Dai Gojū-Nana Kai Hekigai Chōsa (6)- (敗者達 ―第57回壁外調査⑥―)

After watching Eren get swallowed by the Female Titan, Mikasa and Levi follow the brutal monster in the hopes that he’s still alive inside her. As the Scout Regiment tries to recover from the devastating losses of the operation, emotions run high.
name: The Defeated: 57th Expedition Beyond the Walls, Part 6

description:
Japanese title: Hohoemi -Sutohesu-ku Kyūshū (1)- (微笑み ―ストヘス区急襲①―)

After the failed scouting expedition, Eren and his superiors are summoned to the capital. Annie witnesses just how deep corruption runs in the Military Police, and agrees to join Armin in a plot to defy the government—but nothing is really as it seems.
name: Smile: Raid on Stohess District, Part 1

description:
Japanese title: Jihi -Sutohesu-ku Kyūshū (2)- (慈悲 ―ストヘス区急襲②―)

When the identity of the Female Titan is finally revealed, she goes on a rampage within Wall Sina. Eren is hesitant to fight her, but Armin and Mikasa throw themselves into the battle in a desperate attempt to stop the towering monster.
name: Mercy: Raid on Stohess District, Part 2

description:
Japanese title: Kabe -Sutohesu-ku Kyūshū (3)- (壁 ―ストヘス区急襲③―)

Eren goes head-to-head with the Female Titan in a fight that demolishes the Stohess District inside Wall Sina. As the number of casualties skyrockets and Annie tries to escape over the wall, Erwin must deal with the consequences of his plan.
name: Wall: Raid on Stohess District, Part 3

description: OLIVER MUST DECIDE ONCE AND FOR ALL IF HE’S A KILLER OR A HERO — Slade (Manu Bennett) moves forward with his plan to kill one more person in Oliver’s (Stephen Amell) life. While Oliver has fought all year to be more than the killer he once was, when Slade kidnaps someone close to Oliver’s heart, Oliver is pushed to the edge and realizes sometimes it takes doing the unthinkable to stop the monster. Meanwhile, Diggle (David Ramsey) takes on Amanda Waller (guest star Cynthia Addai-Robinson) with a little help from some friends, and Thea (Willa Holland) turns to Roy (Colton Haynes) in her time of need. John Behring directed the episode with story by Greg Berlanti and teleplay by Marc Guggenheim & Andrew Kreisberg.
name: Unthinkable
